p(data-i18n='tree.intro1') Select year and account (revenues or expenses). Click on a fund to see the departments that receive its funding. Click on that department to see its spending or revenue. This page only shows "adopted budgets"; that is, budgets passed by the City Council.

p(data-i18n-html='tree.intro2Html') The <strong>General Fund</strong> — roughly 40% of Sacramento's total budget -- is decided by a <a href="https://www.capradio.org/articles/2023/04/24/how-does-the-sacramento-city-budget-work-heres-what-you-need-to-know/">budget process</a> that includes private and public meetings, surveys, and negotiations. The other 60% of the budget comes from taxes, ballot measures, grants, fees, and other sources.
